---

## Key technical learnings

1. Keeping batch scope logic centralized (`selected` vs `all visible`) reduces integration risk when switching from mock to API behavior.
2. Toast notifications provide clearer, less intrusive feedback than top-down banners for repetitive batch workflows.
3. Partial-success response shapes are essential for cadence workflows where some items are intentionally skipped.

